article.headline: Houston cruises to win over UCF, 82-58

images.name: A. Davis made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by M. Williams.
images.caption: 1H (17:53) UCF A.J. Davis made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Matt Williams.

article.linkText: Houston cruises to win over UCF, 82-58
article.story: HOUSTON -- Devonta Pollard scored 16 points to help lead Houston to a lopsided 82-58 win over Central Florida on Saturday. Danrad Knowles and LeRon Barnes each scored 13 and Damyean Dotson finished with 12 points for the Cougars (18-7, 8-5 American Conference), who have won five of six and crept to within a game-and-a-half of first place in the American Conference standings. Matt Williams led the Knights with 13 points (11-12, 5-7). UCF was held to just 6 of 23 from 3-point range and hit only 6 of 13 at the free throw line. Houston closed the first half on an 18-8 run and led 40-25 at the break. Barnes hit a 3-pointer and Pollard made a pair at the line to make it 45-25, and Eric Weary Jr. hit a layup with 44 seconds left for an 80-55 lead, the Cougars largest of the game.
